title: Bumper crowds at Kuranda Fest
text:
Weather: Cairns 19 °C - 28 °C . Shower or two. News Bumper crowds clown around at Kuranda Festival by: What are these? Locals Kirt Bell and Hayley-Anne Hill enjoying Kuranda Festival. PICTURE: STEWART McLEAN Source: News Limited 
THE circus looks set to stay in Kuranda after the village’s annual festival attracted bumper crowds and rave reviews at the weekend. 
A record 5000 people clowned around at the circus-themed event yesterday, which featured roving performers, workshops, a motorcycle show, eating competitions, the Bash of the Barron River Raft Race and the inaugural Croc Swim. 
On the back of this year’s success, Tourism Kuranda executive officer Marc Sleeman said circus elements would be incorporated into future events. 
“We’re a pretty quirky and unique bunch of people here and it really brings out the colour of the village,” he said. Kuranda Fire fighters Michael Douglas and James Ralston show brothers Heath, 5, and Rhys, 8, the gear they use. PICTURE: STEWART McLEAN Source: News Limited
